description._content: Description: Large Troodos Pine - Pinus nigra var. Karamanica outside Government Cottage Troodos, 10 ft .6" in girth in 1929. Troodos Forest, Elevation 5,300 feet. Location: Cyprus Date: 1929 Description: Wellingtonia - Sequoia gigantea near Government Cottage Troodos, in 1929. About 40 years old, Troodos Forest, Elevation 5,275 feet. Location: Cyprus Date: 1929 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/698 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown.
